Thank you again for your ongoing support and patience.

post_text: Thank you to everyone that joined us this afternoon for our District 86 Town Hall Meeting to discuss the upcoming 2020-2021 school year. We were able to answer some of your questions live during the broadcast, but we wrote down all of your questions and will post the complete Questions & Answers document later this week on the District website, Facebook, and Twitter. Illinois State Board of Education, CDC, and the Illinois Department of Public Health (IDPH). The plan will be constantly updated as new information from these agencies are provided. District 86 parents and guardians will be called in the next two weeks to finalize student registrations and receive feedback to help us as we begin to prepare class rosters and schedules.

post_text: Student registration for the 2020-2021 school year is available online on our website at https://www.joliet86.org/students-parents/student-registration/. Due to the school closure, Kindergarten Registration, originally scheduled in April, has been cancelled. Please register your child online. If your child is currently a Marycrest Student, click on the link for a returning student. If your child will be attending a District 86 school for the first time, click on the new student link. Thank you!

post_text: We encourage you to complete your 2020 Census online at www.my2020census.gov or by phone at (844) 330-2020. If you prefer, paper census materials will be mailed out in mid-April. The collected data impacts many aspects of our community for programs that are critical for our schools and students, including special education, after-school, classroom technology, and school breakfast/lunch programs. Additional census materials are posted on our website at https://www.joliet86.org/students-parents/census-2020-information/. Thank you for supporting our students!

The Board of School Inspectors will recognize Freddie and his coaches at their Board of School Inspectors meeting in April.

Currently we have 35 TECHsperts at Culbertson, Cunningham, Eisenhower, Forest Park, Sandburg, Taft, Thigpen, and Woodland schools to support our elementary schools. post_text: Eisenhower and Washington Academy are currently accepting student applications for the 2020-2021 school year. The programs accept students in first through eighth grades who demonstrate average or above academic achievement and positive behavior. There are approximately 56 openings for first grade, 75 openings for sixth grade and a limited number of openings for grades 2-5 and grades 7-8. The programs are within the Joliet Public School System with no additional fees. Students must reside within the boundaries of Joliet District 86. Application materials are available at https://www.joliet86.org/file.aspx?DocumentId=11804 and https://www.joliet86.org/file.aspx?DocumentId=11803. Applications are due by March 20, 2020. Please call Eisenhower (grades 1-5) at 815-723-0233 or Washington (grades 6-8) at 815-727-5271 for more information.

post_text:
The magnet program at Forest Park Individual Education (I.E.) School and the I.E. program housed at Hufford Junior High are accepting student applications for the 2020-2021 school year. The schools offer a unique educational program based on Adlerian Individual Psychology. The schools are founded on Raymond Corsini's 4Rs: Responsibility, Respectfulness, Resourcefulness, and Responsiveness and focus on a balance of academics, social skills, and creativity.

Parents must commit to the magnet school’s philosophy, including signing a parent contract, and attending four parenting sessions during the school year. Enrollment is open to students residing within the boundaries of Joliet Public Schools District 86. Interested parents with children in grades K-5 may call (815) 723-0414 or (815) 725-3540 for students in grades 6-8 to inquire about the open enrollment process.

post_text: Eisenhower Academy and the Academy Program at Washington Junior High are now accepting student applications for the 2020-2021 school year. Eisenhower, a 2016 National Blue Ribbon School, serves students in grades 1-5 while Washington Academy serves students in grades 6-8. All students must demonstrate average or above academic achievement, positive behavior, and live within Joliet Public Schools District 86 boundaries. Space is limited. The deadline for applications is March 20, 2020. The applications can be found here https://www.joliet86.org/file.aspx?DocumentId=11804 or https://www.joliet86.org/file.aspx?DocumentId=11803. For more information, please call Eisenhower at (815) 723-0233 or Washington at (815) 727-5271.

post_text: The Board of School Inspectors approved a new three-year contract last night for the Joliet #86 School Related Personnel Council, American Federation of Teachers, Local 604. The three-year wage settlement provides employees with an average wage increase of 3.5% in each year of the contract. The new agreement is retroactive to the beginning of this school year. This bargaining unit serves approximately 293 employees and is composed of paraprofessional employees, secretarial and clerical employees, and nutritional services employees.

post_text: It's been a year since we launched "Let's Talk." This platform is an additional communication tool, available 24 hours a day, seven days a week, for anyone to submit a question, comment, concern, suggestion, or compliment about District 86. We appreciate all the feedback. Strawberry milk is now a daily item on our school menus thanks to a suggestion from a junior high student! The link is available on our website at https://www.joliet86.org/district-info/lets-talk/
